quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  9,94,"They will make excuses to you ňĻbelieversňļ when you return to them. Say, ‚ÄúMake no excuses, ňĻforňļ we will not believe you. Allah has already informed us about your ňĻtrueňļ state ňĻof faithňļ. Your ňĻfutureňļ deeds will be observed by Allah and His Messenger as well. And you will be returned to the Knower of the seen and unseen, then He will inform you of what you used to do.‚ÄĚ"
  9,95,"When you return, they will swear to you by Allah so that you may leave them alone. So leave them alone‚ÄĒthey are truly evil. Hell will be their home as a reward for what they have committed"
  9,96,"They will swear to you in order to please you. And even if you are pleased with them, Allah will never be pleased with the rebellious people"
  9,97,"The nomadic Arabs ňĻaround Medinaňļ are far worse in disbelief and hypocrisy, and less likely to know the laws revealed by Allah to His Messenger. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  9,98,"And among the nomads are those who consider what they donate to be a loss and await your misfortune. May ill-fortune befall them! And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  9,99,"However, among the nomadic Arabs are those who believe in Allah and the Last Day, and consider what they donate as a means of coming closer to Allah and ňĻreceivingňļ the prayers of the Messenger. It will certainly bring them closer. Allah will admit them into His mercy. Surely Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"